Larger stores refer to those with a size greater than 10,000 square feet;
The term "larger stores" can be interpreted based on the context of store size in the database, generally indicating a significant physical presence;
Sorting "from the most recently opened to the oldest" means the opening dates are in descending order.

sql:
SELECT manager_name, performance_rating
FROM managers
WHERE performance_rating > (SELECT AVG(performance_rating) FROM managers);

SELECT DISTINCT s.store_id, s.store_name
FROM stores s
JOIN promotions p ON s.store_id = p.store_id
WHERE p.promotion_effectiveness_score < (
    SELECT AVG(promotion_effectiveness_score) FROM promotions
);

SELECT DISTINCT sa.store_id
FROM sales sa
WHERE sa.sale_date IN (SELECT holiday_date FROM holidays);

